01/21/2016: Moved rig from to Tiber; KC 102 #2. Prepared and commenced running 36" conductor from surface to 324'. Commenced unloading vessel. Suspended offloading of vessels due to inclement weather conditions.

Note: On 01/21/2016 @ 4:07 PM; Dave Atkins (Chevron Lead DSM) notified Mr. Royce Buford and Mr. Carl Matte (BSEE) of delay in upcoming BOP pressure test; which would be starting on 01/24/2016.

01/22/2016: Installed Bullseyes / 4" NPT nipples to 36" Low Pressure Housing (LPH). Tripped in hole (TIH) on 6-5/8" drill pipe to 4;055'. Set positioning transponders and calibrated acoustic array. 

01/23/2016: Jetted 36" Conductor from 4;339' to 4;635'.

01/24/2016: Jetted 36" Conductor from 4;635 to 4651'. Released CADA (Cam Action Drill Ahead) tool and drilled 30" x 32" hole from 4;651' to 5;295'.

01/25/2016: Drilled 30" x 32" hole section from 5;295' to 6;050'. TOH (trip out of hole) with 30" x 32" BHA. Ran 28" casing and landed 28" casing out in supplemental adaptor in LPWH (Low Pressure Wellhead) with shoe depth at 5;998'.

01/26/2016: Pumped 602 bbls of 12.4 ppg nitrogen foamed lead cement until returns observed at surface. After returns verified; pumped 168 bbls of non-foamed tail cement at 16.4 ppg. Displaced tail cement to within 75' of 28" shoe with 162 bbls of seawater. Float did not hold. Held pressure and WOC (wait on cement) until set. Performed flow check. No flow. TOH with landing string and 4-1/2" inner string. TIH (tripped in hole) with 26" drilling BHA to tag TOC (top of cement) at 5;963'. Drilled out shoe track and 26" hole section to 6;607'.

01/27/2016: Drilled 26" hole from 6;607' to 7;000' with 10.5 ppg PAD (pump and dump) mud. Drilled ahead from 7;000' to 7;920' with 11.5 ppg PAD mud. Top of salt (TOS) was seen at 7;840'. Observed loss of torque at 7;920' followed with loss of pump pressure. BHA twisted off. Displaced hole to 12.5 ppg and TOH to surface. Made up 11-3/4" overshot assembly with 18" lip guide and TIH to top of fish at 7;837'. Latched on fish and TOH.

01/28/2016: Continued to TOH with fish from 7;837' to surface. M/U new 26" bit and TIH with BHA. Drilled from 7;920' to 7;957'. Torque dropped off and pressure dropped. BHA twisted off. Pumped 12.5 ppg mud and TOH from 7;799' to 6;880'.

01/29/2016: TOH from 6;880' to surface. M/U 11-3/4" overshot assembly with 18" lip guide. TIH to top of fish at 7;801' and latch on to fish. TOH to surface with fish. TIH with 26" drilling BHA and continued to drill 26" hole from 7;957' to 7;980'.

01/30/2016: Drilled 26" hole from 7;980' to 8726'. Observed pressure drop (Wash in Jar mandrel later confirmed). Spotted 16.0 ppg pill on bottom. Pulled back to 8;577' and circulated 1-1/2 hole volume with 12.5 ppg PAD mud. TOH and washed LPWH with seawater. Stabbed 22" x 23" casing into LPWH. Rigged up to run 4-1/2" inner string.

01/31/2016: Tripped in hole (TIH) with 4-1/2" inner string and made up wellhead running tool to 18-3/4" high pressure wellhead (HPWH). TIH with 22" x 23" casing on 6-5/8" landing string. Landed out HPWH into low pressure wellhead housing (LPWH). Circulated 1.5 times annular volume. Mud weight was 16.0 ppg water based mud.

02/01/2016: Tripped out of hole (TOH) with 4-1/2" inner string to HPWH. Flush HPWH. Pulled out of HPWH; and moved rig 500' off location. Picked up (P/U) two joints of riser. Skidded BOP over to well center. Connected riser and splashed BOP. Tested choke and kill lines to 250 psi/ 12;650 psi for 5 minutes. Tested rigid conduits and boost line to 5;000 psi for 5 minutes. Good test. Ran riser from surface to 1;258'. Pressure tests were performed using 8.6 ppg seawater.

02/02/2016: Continued running BOP on marine riser from 1;258' to 4;188'.

02/03/2016: P/U slip joint; pup joint; and landing joint. Installed drape hoses. Pressure tested to 5;000 psi for 5 minutes; good test. Installed choke; kill; and boost drape hoses. Pressure tested choke and kill lines to 250 psi/ 12;650 psi for 5 minutes; good test. Pressure tested boost line to 4;500 psi for 5 minutes; good test. Pressure tests were performed using 8.6 ppg seawater.

02/04/2016: Installed storm loop clamp and multiplex control system (MUX) lines. Latched up BOP to Tiber 4 wellhead at 18:00 hrs. Performed overpull of 1;000 lbs. Performed slump test by setting down 590;000 lbs on wellhead to confirm good latch. Performed deadman test against the upper blind shear ram to 1;000 psi for 5 minutes. Performed wellhead connector test to 1;000 psi and 22" casing test to 4;485 psi. Stroked out telescopic joint. Laid out telescopic joint and rigged down (R/D) riser running tool. P/U diverter. Pressure tests were performed using 8.6 ppg seawater.

02/05/2016: Landed and locked diverter. R/D riser running equipment. TIH with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA and BOP test tool (BOPTT). Pressure tested blind shear rams (BSR) against BOPTT to 250 psi/ 10;600 psi for 5 minutes. Function tested BSRs from Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod. TOH and R/B BOPTT. TIH with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA from 478' to 2;559'. Note: Pressure tested choke and kill manifold and associated valves offline to 250 psi/ 7;000 psi or 250 psi/ 10;600 psi. Pressure tests were performed using 8.6 ppg seawater.

"},{"   ":104,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084005500,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-04-03","TEXT_REMARK":"04/03/2016: Performed sidewall cores with Schlumberger wireline run #6 (Mechanical Sidewall Coring Tool or MSCT) from 28;722' WLM to 28;588' WLM (25 of 25 samples completed; total of 75 out of 75 possible core samples completed). Pulled out of hole (POOH) with run #6 to surface. Laid down (L/D) MSCT toolstring. Recovered 73 cores of 75 attempts. Rigged down (R/D) wireline equipment. Tripped in hole (TIH) with 5" cement stinger from surface to 22;861' MD. Function tested Upper and Lower Blind Shear Rams (BSR) from Toolpusher's Panel; Yellow Pod; and from Driller's Panel; Blue Pod. Function test LBSRs from the Bridge using the acoustic signal. Function tested BOP from Driller's Panel; Blue Pod; and from Toolpusher's Panel; Yellow Pod. Function tested diverter from Driller's Panel. 

04/04/2016: TIH with 5" cement stinger to 31;360'. Circulated Modular Formation Dynamics Tester (MDT) fluid into 14" shoe. Tripped out of hole (TOH) to 28;170'; circulated MDT fluid to surface through choke/kill lines using 15.2 ppg SBM. Swept stack. TIH with 5" cement stinger to 31;360'. Pumped and displaced 1;000' silica blend plug and abandon (P&A) plug #1 from 31;360' to 30;360'. TOH to 30;318'.

Note: Mr. John Gillespie (Chevron) received approval from Mr. Mark Osterman (BSEE) to postpone BOP testing until the three open hole plugs are completed for the abandonment APM.

04/05/2016: At 30;360'; pumped and displaced 1;250' silica blend P&A plug #2 from 30;360' to 29;110'. TOH to 29;110'. Pumped and displaced 1;250' silica blend P&A plug #3 from 29;100' to 27;860'. TOH to 27;640' and circulated bottoms up. Performed BOP pressure test on 6-5/8" drill pipe from the Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod. Tested Annulars and associated valves to 250 psi/ 6;600 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested pipe rams and associated valves to 250 psi/ 10;600 psi 5 minutes each. Positive pressure tested cement P&A plug #3 to 1;700 psi. Current mud weight 15.2 ppg SBM.

04/06/2016: Positive pressure tested cement P&A plug #3 to 1;700 psi. Results were unsatisfactory. TOH to 3;924' with 5" cement stinger. TIH to 14;065' with 5" cement stinger.

Note: Mr. John Gillespie (Chevron) received approval on 04/06/2016 at 6:17 PM; from Mark Osterman (BSEE); to install an additional 1;000' cement plug directly on top of plug #3 after tagging plug #3. The plug will be tested prior to setting a retainer 50' - 100' above the plug.

04/07/2016: TIH with 5" cement stinger; tagged cement plug #3 @ 28;525'. Circulated bottoms up. Pumped and displaced 1;500' silica blend P&A plug #3A from 28;525' to 27;025'. TOH to 20;853.

Note: Mr. John Gillespie (Chevron) received approval on 04/07/2016 at 1:58 PM; from Mark Osterman (BSEE); as per note: "Permission granted to increase the cement plug length from 1000' to 1500' (plug 3a). In addition it is approved to set the cement retainer and plug 4 50' to 100' above the plug 3a's TOC. PE certification must be obtained for these revised procedures. You may commence revised operations based on email confirmation from the PE that he will certify the revisions. An RPM for these revisions must be submitted within 72 hours. The RPM must include PE certification of the revised procedures."

04/08/2016: TOH to 3;797'. Pressure test UBSR; 14" casing and P&A cement plug #3a with 15.2 ppg SBM to 250/1;700 psi 5/30 mins with cement unit. Test satisfactory. TOH from 3;797' to surface. Function tested diverter from Toolpusher's Panel. Function tested UBSR and LBSR from Toolpusher Panel; Blue Pod; and from Driller's Panel; Yellow Pod. P/U 13-3/8" EZSVB; TIH from surface to 13;124'.

04/09/2016: TIH with 13-3/8" EZSVB to 26;914'; set at 26;914'. Released running tool from EZSVB and performed 35k slack off test. Performed positive pressure test to 1;000 psi for 15 mins. Performed negative test on EZSVB to 2;589 psi. Control u-tubed Base oil out of drill pipe and reverse circulated.
"},{"   ":105,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084005500,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-04-10","TEXT_REMARK":"04/10/2016: Mixed and pumped 150 bbls of cement and displaced plug #4 with 772 bbls of 15.2 ppg SBM. Tripped out of hole (TOH) from 26;909' to 25;080'. TOH with EZSV running tool from 25;132' to 23;774'. Performed stripping drill. Pumped slug. TOH with 13-3/8" EZSV running tool from 23;774'to 18;505'. Spotted 75 bbls Hi-vis pill from 18;505' to 18;005'. Mixed and pumped 238 bbls of cement and displaced plug #5 with 466 bbls of 15.2 ppg. P/U to 16;705' and circulated foam ball down drill string. TOH to 6;584'. Made up Multipurpose Tool (MPT) and TIH from 6;584' to 9;243'.

Note: Mr. Ian Nott (Chevron) was granted a 24 hour extension to test the Lower BSR from Mr. Royce Buford (BSEE) via email on 04/10/2016 at 08:02 PM.

04/11/2016: Continued to TIH with MPT from 9;243' to 10;908'. Pulled wear bushing and TOH from 10;908' to 3;741'. Performed pressure test on Lower Blind Shear Rams to 250/1;800 psi for 5/15 minutes with 15.2 ppg SBM. TIH from 3;787' to 6;130' and spotted 50 bbls Hi-Vis pill from 6;130' to 5;300'. TOH to plug #6 setting depth of 5;900'. Mixed and pumped 338 bbls of cement and displaced with 122 bbls of 15.2 ppg SBM. TOH to 4;900'. Displaced well from 15.2 ppg SBM to 8.6 ppg seawater. TOH from 4;900' to surface.

04/12/2016: Rigged up riser handling equipment. Unlatched wellhead connector at 12:50 hrs. Pulled BOP on riser from 4;183' to 2;908'

04/13/2016: Continued pulling BOP on marine riser from 2;908' to surface. Landed BOP on the beams at 07:30 hrs. Skidded BOP to the aux rotary and jetted BOP on the aux rotary. Skidded BOP to the aft port side of the moonpool to the setback area and secured for transit. Departed KC 102 (Tiber 4) enroute to GC640 Tahiti PC001 at 12:00 hrs.

"}]
